title: SFH leads delegation to visit Taichung
content_text:
p>
	The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, will depart for Taichung 
	tomorrow afternoon (July 30) for a duty visit. The visit will include 
	leading a Hong Kong delegation to attend the Hong Kong-Taichung intercity 
	forum and visiting Chinese medicine facilities. The Hong Kong delegation 
	will comprise members of the Chinese Medicine Development Committee. In the morning on July 31, Dr Ko will lead the Hong Kong delegation to 
	attend the 2014 Hong Kong-Taichung Intercity Forum to be held in Taichung

and co-organised by the Hong Kong Economic, Trade and Cultural Office 
	(Taiwan) and the Taichung City Government. With one of the themes being 
	"Inheriting traditional essence ． Pioneering medical highlights", Dr Ko will 
	deliver a speech in the forum to introduce the direction and long-term 
	strategy of Hong Kong in promoting the development of Chinese medicine 
	services. In the afternoon of the same day, Dr Ko and the delegation will visit China 
	Medical University in Taichung. They will visit the museum on traditional

Medical University in Taichung. They will visit the museum on traditional 
	Chinese medicine and a laboratory of Hong Kong Chinese Materia Medica 
	Standards in the university, as well as the Department of the Traditional 
	Chinese Medicine of the China Medical University Hospital. They will also 
	call on the Chancellor of the university and relevant personnel. In the morning on Friday (August 1), Dr Ko and the delegation will visit a 
	factory of a Chinese medicines manufacturer and Taichung Tzu Chi Hospital.

	Dr Ko and the delegation will return to Hong Kong in the afternoon on
